Topic: HCF & LCM (VERY IMPORTANT 🔥)
1️⃣ Clear Theory (Easy Language)

👉 HCF (Highest Common Factor)
= Largest number that divides all given numbers

👉 LCM (Lowest Common Multiple)
= Smallest number divisible by all given numbers

2️⃣ Methods to Find HCF & LCM
🔹 Prime Factorization Method

Break numbers into primes

Example:
12 = 2 × 2 × 3
18 = 2 × 3 × 3

👉 HCF = Common lowest powers → 2 × 3 = 6
👉 LCM = All highest powers → 2² × 3² = 36

🔹 Division Method (Fast)

Use for larger numbers (Railway exams)

3️⃣ Important Formula

👉 HCF × LCM = Product of numbers

(Only for 2 numbers)

🧠 Quick Tricks
HCF = smallest factor
LCM = biggest multiple
If numbers are prime → HCF = 1
Use prime factorization for clarity
